Assuming that the lifeguard would want to help, the 5 stages they would go through is: noticing the emergency, being able to interpret that the event is an emergency, must assume the responsibility on themselves to help, come up with a working strategy, and finally, be able to implement the strategy successfully. Thought the 5 stages differ, the common factor that would prevent them from occurring is the presence of other, as it can be distracting in many ways.


